    • run

      public void run()
      When an object implementing interface Runnable is used to create a thread, starting the thread causes the object's run method to be called in that separately executing thread.

      The general contract of the method run is that it may take any action whatsoever. A thread is used to read object from every player. It starts immediately after the connection.

      Specified by:
      run in interface java.lang.Runnable
      See Also:
      Thread.run()
